Uses of Package
org.jamwiki

  • Packages that use org.jamwiki 
    Package Description
    org.jamwiki
    The org.jamwiki package contains the core interfaces and classes needed for JAMWiki to function.
    org.jamwiki.db
    Provides classes needed for all database interaction.
    org.jamwiki.migrate
    Provides classes needed for XML import/export.
    org.jamwiki.model
    Provides basic objects for use on the Wiki, including WikiUser, Topic, TopicVersion, etc.
    org.jamwiki.parser
    The org.jamwiki.parser package contains the interfaces, abstract classes, and utility classes needed to implement a parser for JAMWiki.
    org.jamwiki.parser.bliki
    Provides an alternative parser for JAMWiki, developed with the Bliki Java Wikipedia API.
    org.jamwiki.parser.image  
    org.jamwiki.parser.jflex
    The org.jamwiki.parsers.jflex package contains the default JAMWiki parser and supporting classes, implementing the Mediawiki Wiki syntax.
    org.jamwiki.search
    Provides a framework for implementing JAMWiki search.
    org.jamwiki.servlets
    Provides classes that work with the Spring Framework to process HTTP requests and to then redirect appropriately.
    org.jamwiki.utils
    Provides various general utility classes including encryption, caching, and logging.
    org.jamwiki.web.utils  
  • Classes in org.jamwiki used by org.jamwiki 
    Class and Description
    JAMWikiParser
    Interface to be used when implementing new parsers.
    SearchEngine
    This interface provides all methods needed for interacting with a search engine.
    WikiBase.UPLOAD_STORAGE
    Enum indicating where uploaded files are stored.
    WikiConfiguration
    The WikiConfiguration class provides the infrastructure for retrieving configuration values.
    WikiMessage
    This class is a utility class useful for storing messages key and object values that can later be displayed using the jstl fmt:message tag.
    WikiVersion
    Utility class that holds the current Wiki version constant and provides methods for comparing Wiki versions.
